1
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:20,291
[NARRATOR] On the outside,
we look the same.

2
00:00:20,375 --> 00:00:23,166
And yet, men call us monsters.

3
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:26,125
We are naught but
shadows lurking in between eras,

4
00:00:26,208 --> 00:00:28,166
but if we are
destined to perish,

5
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:31,416
then I shall fall with
the cherry blossoms.

6
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:32,541
Yes.

7
00:00:32,625 --> 00:00:34,833
I shall fall with
the cherry blossoms.

8
00:01:11,041 --> 00:01:12,583
[HACHIROU]
I can't be certain,

9
00:01:12,666 --> 00:01:15,875
but I think we might have
arrived at a different "now,"

10
00:01:15,958 --> 00:01:19,250
altered from the "now" where
we faced the Joujinshuu,

11
00:01:19,333 --> 00:01:21,333
and lost our companions.

12
00:01:22,458 --> 00:01:25,000
No matter what world
we find ourselves in,

13
00:01:25,083 --> 00:01:28,125
we can't stand by
as Joujin destroys it!

14
00:01:28,208 --> 00:01:30,291
Not while we're
still able to fight!

15
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:16,375
You would interfere
in our affairs?

16
00:03:18,416 --> 00:03:19,833
[laughs]

17
00:03:19,916 --> 00:03:22,916
It'd be rude of us to
turn down free entertainment.

18
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,791
[KUJAKU] I don't know who you
people are, other than fools.

19
00:03:26,875 --> 00:03:28,125
Ready?

20
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:30,000
We'll start with the one
that's the biggest threat.

21
00:03:44,541 --> 00:03:46,416
[yells]

22
00:03:51,666 --> 00:03:54,750
[KUJAKU]
Impossible.

23
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:55,791
[ITARU gasps]

24
00:03:57,708 --> 00:04:00,041
My Destiny's Passage
will make short work of you!

25
00:04:03,250 --> 00:04:04,333
You knew?

26
00:04:18,041 --> 00:04:19,458
Damn you.

27
00:04:19,541 --> 00:04:22,583
Your attack was a feint--
you used me to distract them!

28
00:04:37,625 --> 00:04:39,833
[NEIRICHIOU growls]

29
00:04:47,375 --> 00:04:48,916
Neirichiou!

30
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,208
You...

31
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:53,708
[NEIRICHIOU growl]

32
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,333
[NEIRICHIOU grunts]

33
00:05:03,416 --> 00:05:09,958
[NEIRICHIOU screams]

34
00:05:20,458 --> 00:05:23,583
Who are you? Tell me your names!

35
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:25,208
Kouga Hachirou.

36
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:26,916
Iga Hibiki.

37
00:05:31,083 --> 00:05:34,833
[JOUJIN] Well, they
proved to be worthless.

38
00:05:34,916 --> 00:05:37,125
Killed so easily.

39
00:05:38,625 --> 00:05:39,916
[JOUJIN]
What's wrong?

40
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:42,000
I stand before you now.

41
00:05:42,083 --> 00:05:44,750
Won't you use your
"eye magic" on me?

42
00:05:44,833 --> 00:05:45,833
Hachirou.

43
00:05:45,916 --> 00:05:47,208
I can't.

44
00:05:47,291 --> 00:05:49,583
My Spearing Eye
won't work against him.

45
00:05:49,666 --> 00:05:51,000
Well then, I'll try.

46
00:05:51,083 --> 00:05:53,083
No, that last time.

47
00:05:53,166 --> 00:05:55,958
Your technique only worked
because he was caught off guard.

48
00:05:56,041 --> 00:05:57,458
[HIBIKI growls]

49
00:05:57,541 --> 00:05:58,708
Joujin.

50
00:05:58,791 --> 00:06:01,333
No matter what world you're in,
we won't allow

51
00:06:01,416 --> 00:06:04,000
your wicked desires to
ever come to fruition!

52
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:05,250
Oh?

53
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:07,750
No matter what world I'm in?

54
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:10,791
So, what happened
to me in this "other world"

55
00:06:10,875 --> 00:06:12,833
to which you refer?

56
00:06:12,916 --> 00:06:14,750
You met with a gruesome death.

57
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:18,125
[JOUJIN]
I died, and then what happened?

58
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:19,958
Nothing.

59
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:22,791
You died, and all your
scheming lead to failure.

60
00:06:22,875 --> 00:06:25,625
Then that possibility
is the only one you have seen?

61
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:26,750
It was.

62
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,083
I see.

63
00:06:28,166 --> 00:06:29,625
[chuckles]

64
00:06:29,708 --> 00:06:30,916
[HACHIROU]
Why do you laugh?

65
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:34,000
[laughs]
That's enough!

66
00:06:34,083 --> 00:06:35,000
Begone!

67
00:06:35,083 --> 00:06:36,083
[gasps] 

68
00:06:36,166 --> 00:06:37,791
You know nothing.

69
00:06:37,875 --> 00:06:41,041
No matter the fate that
bound us in another world,

70
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:43,875
we are but strangers
in this one.

71
00:06:43,958 --> 00:06:46,833
I will achieve my
ambitions with Murakumo!

72
00:06:46,916 --> 00:06:48,750
I cannot be stopped!

73
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:51,958
Perhaps, or perhaps not.

74
00:06:52,041 --> 00:06:55,416
Because in this world, you know
nothing of our final technique!

75
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:56,875
Your what?

76
00:07:01,541 --> 00:07:03,041
[gasps]

77
00:07:09,666 --> 00:07:12,541
I've never seen
a power like this before!

78
00:07:24,208 --> 00:07:26,000
I'll handle the rest of it.

79
00:07:26,083 --> 00:07:27,416
Thank you.

80
00:07:27,500 --> 00:07:31,458
So, try to tell me
what it's like, best you can.

81
00:07:31,541 --> 00:07:33,416
[HIBIKI sighs]

82
00:07:33,500 --> 00:07:36,083
There's love, caring.

83
00:07:36,166 --> 00:07:39,250
Plus pain and sorrow.

84
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:41,375
All those feelings combined.

85
00:07:42,791 --> 00:07:45,083
Perhaps it's connected
to the contradictory powers

86
00:07:45,166 --> 00:07:47,083
you originally possessed.

87
00:07:47,166 --> 00:07:49,583
Something that channeled
those diverse feelings,

88
00:07:49,666 --> 00:07:52,333
and distilled them into
a strength unmatched.

89
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:53,541
But...

90
00:07:53,625 --> 00:07:56,291
If that's how it works,
why aren't we able

91
00:07:56,375 --> 00:07:58,333
to control the power ourselves?

92
00:07:58,416 --> 00:08:00,083
Because of those emotions.

93
00:08:00,166 --> 00:08:02,041
They're rooted in
violence and passion,

94
00:08:02,125 --> 00:08:03,958
and can't be controlled.

95
00:08:04,041 --> 00:08:05,958
It's a power
that's fueled by joy,

96
00:08:06,041 --> 00:08:09,416
melancholy, and madness.

97
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:11,750
[GORONE]
I find it hard to comprehend.

98
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:14,666
Why would the technique you
both created be so powerful,

99
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:18,041
yet unable to bring
you happiness?

100
00:08:18,125 --> 00:08:20,583
The entire equation is unfair.

101
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:21,958
[gasps]

102
00:08:24,708 --> 00:08:28,083
Ouka can evolve,
this is the first stage.

103
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:29,500
[GORONE]
Yes.

104
00:08:29,583 --> 00:08:31,541
What we've seen of the technique
could easily be eclipsed

105
00:08:31,625 --> 00:08:34,125
by the intense brilliance
of its true form.

106
00:08:35,583 --> 00:08:38,583
[HIBIKI]
The brilliance of its true form.

107
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:41,500
[JOUJIN]
This is your ultimate technique?

108
00:08:41,583 --> 00:08:42,708
[HIBIKI gasps]

109
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,291
[JOUJIN]
Behold.

110
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:07,208
Look upon the destruction
your ability has wrought.

111
00:09:07,291 --> 00:09:08,583
[HACHIROU gasps]

112
00:09:08,666 --> 00:09:10,000
[HIBIKI growls]

113
00:09:12,791 --> 00:09:16,291
In the end, my weakness
brings me shame.

114
00:09:16,375 --> 00:09:18,791
I'll never get over the pain of
being unable to defeat you

115
00:09:18,875 --> 00:09:21,375
without using the Ouka.

116
00:09:21,458 --> 00:09:23,958
So now... you will kill me?

117
00:09:25,166 --> 00:09:27,291
I will put you down
without mercy.

118
00:09:28,541 --> 00:09:30,333
Die, Joujin.

119
00:10:04,166 --> 00:10:06,625
[HACHIROU] It doesn't
matter what the Ouka is,

120
00:10:06,708 --> 00:10:09,208
we must abstain from
ever using it again.

121
00:10:10,625 --> 00:10:12,791
Yes.

122
00:10:12,875 --> 00:10:16,250
[HACHIROU]
But as long as we're together,

123
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:18,375
we cannot escape its grasp!

124
00:10:19,458 --> 00:10:20,750
I've chosen.

125
00:10:20,833 --> 00:10:22,916
I know what I'm
willing to forfeit.

126
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:26,000
[HIBIKI gasps]
No, don't leave again!

127
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:31,958
[HIBIKI gasps]

128
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:37,583
[gasps]

129
00:10:39,791 --> 00:10:42,333
[HIBIKI]
No! Give me another chance!

130
00:10:42,416 --> 00:10:44,041
You have to!

131
00:10:46,791 --> 00:10:48,750
[HACHIROU grunts]

132
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:57,625
Wait. Your Shielding Eye.

133
00:10:57,708 --> 00:10:59,541
Yes, Hachirou.

134
00:10:59,625 --> 00:11:02,625
It's finally time to do what I
should have done long ago.

135
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:21,958
[HACHIROU]
Hibiki!

136
00:11:25,666 --> 00:11:26,875
[HACHIROU]
No...

137
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:33,291
[HIBIKI] Now, you'll never
forget about Ouka.

138
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:34,958
Or leave me behind.

139
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:37,666
[HACHIROU whimpers]

140
00:11:39,333 --> 00:11:41,458
Hibiki..

141
00:11:41,541 --> 00:11:44,500
I'll never stray
from your side again.

142
00:11:44,583 --> 00:11:47,916
I'll be with you, eternally.

143
00:11:50,791 --> 00:11:53,166
[JOUJIN]
Pathetic fools.

144
00:11:57,708 --> 00:12:00,250
[HACHIROU]
Joujin!

145
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:04,750
Tell me, was that display
the best you could muster?

146
00:12:04,833 --> 00:12:06,833
Impossible.

147
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:08,875
I killed you, I'm sure of it.

148
00:12:24,625 --> 00:12:27,791
That can't be. Tenzen?

149
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:34,666
I'm impressed
that you know of him.

150
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:37,833
[HACHIROU]
The Tenzen cherry tree blooms

151
00:12:37,916 --> 00:12:39,708
above Jison'in Village.

152
00:12:39,791 --> 00:12:42,625
They say an immortal ninja
gave the tree its name.

153
00:12:42,708 --> 00:12:44,041
Tenzen.

154
00:12:44,125 --> 00:12:46,083
[HACHIROU]
You mean to tell me he was real?

155
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:50,583
[JOUJIN]
So it would appear.

156
00:12:50,666 --> 00:12:54,291
Now, he lives on within me.

157
00:12:54,375 --> 00:12:55,916
[gasps]

158
00:12:58,166 --> 00:13:01,541
[JOUJIN] I never thought she
would destroy her own eyes.

159
00:13:01,625 --> 00:13:03,291
How very dull.

160
00:13:05,166 --> 00:13:06,208
All right.

161
00:13:06,291 --> 00:13:08,791
She's no threat,
just forget about us.

162
00:13:08,875 --> 00:13:10,541
[JOUJIN]
I will, I assure you.

163
00:13:10,625 --> 00:13:14,250
Of course, if I let you live,
you'll only get in my way.

164
00:13:14,333 --> 00:13:15,500
What?

165
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:22,666
[JOUJIN] Even a single pebble
in the road could cause

166
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:24,250
a man to stumble.

167
00:13:24,333 --> 00:13:27,500
That is why you must be removed.

168
00:13:29,416 --> 00:13:32,458
[yells]

169
00:13:39,791 --> 00:13:42,958
[JOUJIN] The eye magic you
used to defeat Magoroku.

170
00:13:43,041 --> 00:13:47,291
it seems to reflect an enemy's
desire to kill you back on them.

171
00:13:47,375 --> 00:13:50,458
An interesting technique,
to say the very least.

172
00:13:50,541 --> 00:13:52,708
[HACHIROU grunts]

173
00:13:52,791 --> 00:13:55,791
[JOUJIN] And still,
you will not use it on me,

174
00:13:55,875 --> 00:13:58,458
now that all other options
have failed you?

175
00:13:59,958 --> 00:14:02,583
I assume you used it
against me in that other world

176
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:05,875
you spoke of, and it
failed to affect me.

177
00:14:05,958 --> 00:14:06,875
[HACHIROU growls]

178
00:14:06,958 --> 00:14:09,208
[JOUJIN]
I have seen your weakness,

179
00:14:09,291 --> 00:14:11,750
and know precisely
how to exploit it.

180
00:14:11,833 --> 00:14:13,083
[HACHIROU growls]

181
00:14:13,166 --> 00:14:15,291
[HIBIKI]
Hachirou!

182
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:20,000
Hibiki.

183
00:14:20,083 --> 00:14:21,333
[HIBIKI]
Hachirou.

184
00:14:21,416 --> 00:14:22,833
Where are you?

185
00:14:28,708 --> 00:14:30,291
[HIBIKI whines]

186
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:39,000
[JOUJIN yells]

187
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:58,416
[JOUJIN]
Too easy.

188
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,958
Stupid boy.

189
00:15:00,041 --> 00:15:03,041
[HACHIROU] Joujin, aren't
you ashamed of yourself?

190
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:04,583
[JOUJIN]
Hmm?

191
00:15:04,666 --> 00:15:06,750
Keeping yourself alive.

192
00:15:06,833 --> 00:15:09,833
Having to rely on
the power of Tenzen.

193
00:15:09,916 --> 00:15:12,375
The power of a mere ninja?

194
00:15:12,458 --> 00:15:13,833
That's your plan?

195
00:15:13,916 --> 00:15:16,916
To draw out my desire to
kill you with your insults?

196
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:19,125
A feeble attempt at best.

197
00:15:19,208 --> 00:15:20,666
Didn't you know?

198
00:15:20,750 --> 00:15:24,833
Tenzen lusted after Oboro,
leader of the Iga clan.

199
00:15:24,916 --> 00:15:28,750
He tried to rape the woman
he was honor-bound to serve,

200
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:32,041
a despicable monster.

201
00:15:32,125 --> 00:15:34,708
If you realize your ambitions,

202
00:15:34,791 --> 00:15:39,208
but only through the help of a
worthless excuse for a ninja.

203
00:15:39,291 --> 00:15:42,708
Can you honestly take pride in
what you've accomplished?

204
00:15:42,791 --> 00:15:45,250
You're a tenacious one,
I'll give you that much.

205
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:47,083
Hachirou, was it?

206
00:15:47,166 --> 00:15:49,333
It won't work on me.

207
00:15:55,708 --> 00:15:56,916
[gasps]

208
00:15:59,833 --> 00:16:00,750
What?

209
00:16:00,833 --> 00:16:02,000
Stop it!

210
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:12,000
[coughs]

211
00:16:12,083 --> 00:16:16,166
You used... Tenzen's
desire... to kill you?

212
00:16:18,541 --> 00:16:21,500
[JOUJIN groans]

213
00:16:24,708 --> 00:16:26,708
Tenzen. Stop it!

214
00:16:26,791 --> 00:16:28,708
What are you doing?

215
00:16:28,791 --> 00:16:30,208
Hachirou!

216
00:16:30,291 --> 00:16:32,500
Where are you?

217
00:16:32,583 --> 00:16:36,375
[JOUJIN groans]

218
00:16:36,458 --> 00:16:38,000
[TENZEN screeches]

219
00:16:38,083 --> 00:16:40,333
[JOUJIN groans]

220
00:17:27,208 --> 00:17:28,166
Slow down, Chou!

221
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:29,458
Wait up!

222
00:17:34,208 --> 00:17:35,125
[IEMITSU]
In truth.

223
00:17:35,208 --> 00:17:37,583
I don't like my brother,
Tadanaga.

224
00:17:37,666 --> 00:17:40,416
Neither do I believe his story.

225
00:17:40,500 --> 00:17:42,166
He tried to plot rebellion.

226
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:45,000
He not only betrayed me,
but our legacy.

227
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:47,541
I will not abide this treason.

228
00:17:49,666 --> 00:17:51,000
However.

229
00:17:53,416 --> 00:17:56,458
I wonder who
stoked this fire within him.

230
00:17:58,291 --> 00:18:00,583
Our stations were
determined by the outcome

231
00:18:00,666 --> 00:18:02,000
of a ninja battle.

232
00:18:03,208 --> 00:18:05,875
Such an embarrassing
fact about us both,

233
00:18:05,958 --> 00:18:09,250
and one only a handful
of people could have known.

234
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:14,750
He still could not
forgive me, after so long.

235
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:16,291
[TENKAI]
Your Majesty.

236
00:18:16,375 --> 00:18:19,750
In the end, it was all for the
glory of the Tokugawa Clan.

237
00:18:21,250 --> 00:18:24,333
[NARRATOR] Some say Tenkai lived
on for another decade,

238
00:18:24,416 --> 00:18:26,875
eventually surpassing
the century mark,

239
00:18:26,958 --> 00:18:30,166
until he had fulfilled all
of his earthly desires.

240
00:18:37,625 --> 00:18:40,750
Wait! I'm not ready yet.

241
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,125
I...

242
00:18:46,166 --> 00:18:48,333
[NARRATOR] The tenth
year of the Kan'ei Era.

243
00:18:48,416 --> 00:18:50,000
In December of that year.

244
00:18:50,083 --> 00:18:52,541
Tokugawa Tadanaga commits
seppuku by the order

245
00:18:52,625 --> 00:18:54,333
of the Shogun.

246
00:18:54,416 --> 00:18:56,541
A fact that few people
were aware of,

247
00:18:56,625 --> 00:18:59,083
due to the machinations
of the Joujinshuu

248
00:18:59,166 --> 00:19:02,416
was that the true Tadanaga
had died long ago.

249
00:19:04,541 --> 00:19:06,333
[NARRATOR]
And the cherry blossoms,

250
00:19:06,416 --> 00:19:10,916
bloomed and fell several times,
as the seasons rolled on.

251
00:19:13,208 --> 00:19:15,416
[CHILDREN laughing, yelling]

252
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,208
[SAIZOU]
Go for it, Shichigen!

253
00:19:17,291 --> 00:19:18,916
Watch close, Utsutsu!

254
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,375
I won't lose today!

255
00:19:20,458 --> 00:19:23,291
Rui! You should come
and watch with me!

256
00:19:23,375 --> 00:19:25,125
[SHICHIGEN]
Go ahead and make your move!

